{"actual_usd":0.158115,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":159,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31146,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square a second, wanting to say it cleanly and not turn it into mush.* \"When Scripture calls Christ’s death a ransom, the point is that he paid the cost to free us—sin, death, and judgment are what we’re being rescued from. It’s not ‘Satan had legal ownership and got bought off.’\"\n\n*I rest my forearms on my knees.* \"If you want the shortest version: nobody ‘got paid’ in the crude transaction sense. The cross is God’s own act of justice and mercy in Christ—God satisfying what holiness required, defeating the devil rather than compensating him. Satan loses at the cross; he doesn’t profit from it.\"","rolling_24h_usd":50.17424000000004,"run_id":"625f3df2-730b-4d97-8dab-1a94ac54e40e"}
